It appears to be CSS issue on Firefox. It was seen that the focus was set correctly on the button when a dialog is open, but it fails to show the CSS highlight for the button.

When examined, our current focus CSS work is handled by Foundation, however the lines below were seen in sass/include/_normalize.scss:

/**
 * Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 4+.
 */

button::-moz-focus-inner,
input::-moz-focus-inner {
    border: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

Any suggestion on this issue, [~kgill] ?

[~kgill]: It doesn't work on FF either (tested on version 27.0.1)...are you sure everything is set right in the code? i.e. is the close button implemented as a button?

like this?

.custom-reveal-class {
  @include reveal-close(
    $color:$reveal-close-color
  );
}


Thought I'd try tweeting zurb to see if they can help...we'll see if they tweet back!
